data.description: This charming 1922 home seamlessly blends classic character and modern updates. Original hardwood floors, trim, doors, linen and medicine built-ins instantly show off the home's rich history. Three bedrooms, each with walk-in-closets, proves no shortage of space. The clean basement, oversized one-stall garage and shed also provide storage conveniences. Outdoors you will discover your own private oasis. Entertain under the twinkling lights, by the custom firepit, in the refreshing pool, or be challenged to a game of basketball on the expansive driveway. The beautifully maintained landscaping features the work of a professional designer and owner's pride. Modern upgrades ensure comfortable living: tankless water heater and updated plumbing (2020), roof, siding, shed, basement windows, and stone patio (2018), garage door and opener (2020), kitchen appliances and underground sprinkling (2021), driveway and privacy fence (2022). Sitting between 131 and Richmond Park, this location offers easy access to shopping, groceries, and parks. Plus, enjoy peace of mind with lovely neighbors! Seller directs Listing Agent to hold all offers until Monday, February 26th at 12pm.
